data.description: Tucked away in desirable Middle Paxton Township, Central Dauphin School District this spacious Two-Story has endless picturesque views! Welcome to this piece of paradise situated on approximately 1.1 acres near the Susquehanna River. When you arrive, you will be instantly impressed by everything this home has to offer and more. Custom built in 2009 with approximately 3,300 sq. feet of living space, and a bright and open floor plain. You will love to gather in the 24' x 24' Kitchen & Dining Area with full appliance package to remain and newer windows offering lots of natural lighting. The main floor also features a Living Room with tray ceilings, Master Bedroom Suite with a walk-in closet, Master Bath, 2 additional nice size bedrooms, Guest Powder Room, Utility Room, and Laundry Room with the washer & dryer to remain. The second-Floor features 2 large Bedrooms, office, 21’x15’Family Room and a Full Bathroom with soaking tub and separate shower. The ground floor Basement/Garage features 3 areas, all with 10’ ceilings, and removal walls, and entry doors. 40’ x 24’ area with a full bath, 29’ x 20’ area with a half bath, and a 28’ x 8’ area with shelving. The perfect retreat awaits you when you go outdoors, starting with an above ground pool, kids play area, fire pits, lots of green space and near the Susquehanna River with endless water activities. With a fabulous indoor/outdoor flow this is truly a great place to call home. Please call today for your private showing.
